entries.meaning: (law) Severed from the appropriation or possession of a spiritual corporation.
examples: The appropriation may be severed, and the church become disappropriate, two ways.

verbs.description: disappropriate (third-person singular simple present disappropriates, present participle disappropriating, simple past and past participle disappropriated)

entries.meaning: To remove something that has been allocated to someone; often to reassign it elsewhere.
